<h1>Hello, Dreamer!</h1>

<p>Basic Ruby on Rails application with a User Model, Devise for user authentication and S3 bucket to store UserAvatar images.<br>
It uses Sendgrid to email on account verification and password resets.<br><br>

In Production create an AWS S3 bucket, an IAM user and a policy for permissions and the connection.<br><br>

Save what you need in the ENV<br>
$ heroku config:set S3_BUCKET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxx -a devise-sandbox<br>
$ heroku config:set S3_ACCESS_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxx -a devise-sandbox<br>
$ heroku config:set S3_SECRET_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx -a devise-sandbox<br>
</p>

